    <passage>
      <offset>0</offset>
      <text>Dynamics of histone modifications after an acclimatizing HS (ACC) or no HS (NHS) in Col-0 wild type at HSP22.0 (A) and HSP70 (B). Seedlings were subjected to ACC or a control treatment (NHS) 4 d after germination. At the indicated time points after the treatments, ChIP-qPCR was performed with antibodies against H3K9ac, H3K4me3, H3K4me2 and H3. Schematics show positions of regions analyzed. Amplicon positions relative to TSS are HSP22.0: 1, -2570 bp; 2, +235 bp. HSP70: 1, 4192 bp downstream of the 3'UTR; 2, +47 bp. Data shown are averages over three biological replicates. Amplification values were normalized to input, H3 and 4 h NHS region 2. The bottom panel shows the H3 signal normalized to input and 4 h NHS region 2. Squares and triangles within bars mark significant differences (p&lt;0.01 and p&lt;0.05, respectively, Student&#180;s t-test) between ACC and NHS samples of the same time point. Error bars indicate SE.</text>
